by Adam Budofsky

A number of bands today are successfully exploring the intersection of psychedelic, pop, and garage-rock music. Australia’s Tame Impala and King Gizzard and the Lizard Wizard, Britain’s Wytches and Syd Arthur, and America’s Ty Segall and Unknown Mortal Orchestra have bloomed boldly in the past year or two, each with its own unique approach to working the fertile musical ground planted in the ’60s by the Kinks, the 13th Floor
